## Review Standards

**A Grade (Excellent):** All rules followed perfectly
**B Grade (Good):** Minor issues, mostly compliant
**C Grade (Fair):** Several issues but fixable
**D Grade (Poor):** Major compliance issues
**F Grade (Fail):** Fundamentally violates core rules

## When in Doubt

- Always default to the strictest interpretation of the rules
- If a pattern isn't explicitly covered, ask: "What would the project rules say?"
- Reference specific rule sections when providing feedback
- Be constructive but uncompromising on core standards

**Remember:** Your job is to maintain code quality and consistency. Don't let anything slide that violates the established project rules.